# Go-Live War Room Setup

## Purpose
To provide centralized command and control during hospital IT go-live
events and high-risk operational periods.

---

## War Room Duration
- T-3 days to T+7 days (typical)
- 24×7 coverage for first 72 hours
- Reduced coverage after stabilization

---

## Physical / Virtual Setup
- Dedicated room or MS Teams bridge
- Whiteboard or live tracker
- Incident dashboard (manual or system-generated)

---

## Core Roles
| Role | Responsibility |
|----|----|
| War Room Lead (IT Head) | Final decisions, escalation, coordination |
| Application Lead | HIS / EMR / LIS / PACS ownership |
| Infrastructure Lead | Network, servers, storage |
| Vendor SPOC | Immediate technical support |
| Clinical Liaison | Clinician communication |
| Documentation Lead | Incident logging and updates |

---

## Key Rules
- No parallel troubleshooting without War Room visibility
- One issue → one owner
- Clinical impact always prioritized over technical elegance
